---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Integrations from '../components/Integrations.astro';
import Pricing from '../components/Pricing.astro';
---
<Layout title="701am for higher-ed agencies" description="701am for higher-ed agencies — the earned-media engine for higher education. Be the answer in AI, the result in Google, and the name in the press.">
<!-- HERO -->
<header class="ind-hero" id="top">
  <div class="hero-atmos"><div class="grid"></div><div class="glow g1"></div><div class="glow g2"></div><div class="glow g3"></div></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="ind-eyebrow"><a class="bk" href="index.html">701am for Higher&nbsp;Ed</a> / For agencies serving higher education</div>
    <h1>Run earned media for every client — <em class="grad">without the headcount</em>.</h1>
    <p class="isub">You already win higher-ed clients on strategy. 701am is the engine that delivers it — a swarm of agents that researches, earns coverage, and builds AI and search visibility for each institution you serve, scoped and isolated per client. <b>Multiply your team, keep your margin.</b></p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-sparkles"></i>Request early access</button>
      <button class="btn btn-soft btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-player-play"></i>See it work</button>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-stat"><b>One engine</b>, every client — scoped, isolated, and always on</div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- NAMED PROBLEM -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="problem">
    <div class="problem-eyebrow">The capacity problem</div>
    <h2 class="problem-h">Your growth is capped by <em class="grad">how many people you can hire</em>.<br><span class="problem-until">701am lifts the cap.</span></h2>
    <p class="problem-p">Every new institution means more research, more outreach, more reporting — and more headcount eating your margin. 701am gives each client its own scoped workspace where the swarm does the heavy lifting: finding angles, earning coverage, tracking visibility across AI, search, and press. You stay the strategist and the face; the engine handles the volume. The work for one client never bleeds into another.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LANDSCAPE -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">The landscape</div>
    <h2>How agencies scale with 701am.</h2>
    <p>Generic PR treats every client the same. 701am works the channels that actually confer credibility in higher ed.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="landscape">
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--indigo-soft);color:var(--indigo-deep)"><i class="ti ti-layout-grid"></i></div>
      <h3>A workspace per client</h3><p>Each institution gets an isolated workspace with its own context, voice, and history. Nothing leaks between clients.</p><span class="lq">Scoped &amp; <b>client-isolated</b></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--coral-soft);color:var(--coral-deep)"><i class="ti ti-robot"></i></div>
      <h3>The swarm does the volume</h3><p>Research, outreach, monitoring, and reporting run continuously per client — the work that used to need a pod of people.</p><span class="lq">Multiply <b>without hiring</b></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lscard">
      <div class="li" style="background:var(--green-soft);color:var(--green-deep)"><i class="ti ti-discount"></i></div>
      <h3>Your margin, protected</h3><p>Deliver more visibility per client at a fraction of the labor cost — and keep the strategy, relationships, and credit.</p><span class="lq">Keep the <b>margin &amp; the face</b></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DATA STORY -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">What it produces</div>
    <h2>A story a reporter <em class="grad">actually opens</em>.</h2>
    <p>Not a press release. A data-backed angle built from real numbers — the kind that earns coverage and gets cited.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="story">
    <div class="story-h"><i class="ti ti-file-text"></i>Campaign angle<span class="mono">auto-generated · example</span></div>
    <div class="story-b">
      <div class="hl">“Agencies running AI-native earned media delivered 3× the placements per FTE last cycle”</div>
      <div class="meta"><span class="m">Archetype: Benchmark</span><span class="m">Source: Agency benchmark</span><span class="m">Beats: Marketing + agency</span><span class="m live">Status: Illustrative</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
<section class="band wrap">
  <div class="sec-head">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Who it’s for</div>
    <h2>Built for teams like <em class="grad">yours</em>.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="forwho">
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-briefcase"></i><span class="ft"><b>Enrollment-marketing agencies</b> serving multiple institutions at once</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-building-store"></i><span class="ft"><b>Higher-ed PR &amp; comms shops</b> that want an earned-media engine, not more hires</span></div>
    <div class="fw"><i class="ti ti-arrows-split"></i><span class="ft"><b>Consultancies</b> ready to add a productized visibility offering to their lineup</span></div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- INTEGRATIONS -->
<Integrations context="agencies" />

<!-- PRICING -->
<Pricing context="agencies" />

<!-- CLOSING -->
<section class="closing">
  <div class="catmos"><div class="cg"></div></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="pill-badge"><span class="tagm">Filed at sunrise</span></div>
    <h2>Be impossible to <em class="grad">miss</em>.</h2>
    <p>701am is opening to a first group of higher-ed teams. Put your name down.</p>
    <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg js-soon"><i class="ti ti-sparkles"></i>Request early access</button>
  </div>
</section>

</div>
</Layout>
